  "texts": [
    "We can now again impose that z and z are related by complex conjugation by combining the solutions (v 1, v 2) and (v 2, v1):z(t) z(t) = v 1 v 2 e -iωt + v2 v1 e iωt.",
    "(85)So to reiterate, our solution strategy was to first solve the linearized dynamics in a larger space where z and z are independent variables, and then project back to the physical space where z and z are related by complex conjugation.",
    "As a final comment, let us mention that the matrix in Eq.",
    "( 84) is non-Hermitian.",
    "Nevertheless, we have assumed that ω is real."
  ],
